</p>
<p>The only rule about an authenticator is that it needs to extend <code>AbstractGuardAuthenticator</code>.
Well, not totally true - if you're building some sort of login form, you can extend
a different class instead: <code>AbstractFormLoginAuthenticator</code> - it extends that other
class, but fills in some details for us.</p>
<p>Hit <code>Command</code>+<code>N</code> - or go to the "Code"-&gt;"Generate" menu - choose "Implement Methods" and
select the first three:</p>
