<h2 id="how-authenticators-work">How Authenticators Work <a class="headerlink" href="login-form-authenticator#how-authenticators-work" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>When we're finished, Symfony will call our authenticator on <em>every single request</em>. Our
job is to:</p>
<ol>
<li>See if the user is submitting the login form, or if this is just some random
request for some random page.</li>
<li>Read the username and password from the request.</li>
<li>Load the User object from the database.</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="getcredentials">getCredentials() <a class="headerlink" href="login-form-authenticator#getcredentials" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>That all starts in <code>getCredentials()</code>. Since this method is called on <em>every</em> request,
we <em>first</em> need to see if the request is a login form submit. We setup our form so
that it POSTs right back to <code>/login</code>. So if the URL is <code>/login</code> and the HTTP method
is <code>POST</code>, our authenticator should spring into action. Otherwise, it should do nothing:
this is just a normal page.</p>
<p>Create a new variable called <code>$isLoginSubmit</code> Set that to <code>$request-&gt;getPathInfo()</code> -
that's the URL - <code>== '/login' &amp;&amp; $request-&gt;isMethod('POST')</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="23e75d0cc3">
    <div class="meta">
