</p>
<p>If you return <code>null</code> from <code>getCredentials()</code>, Symfony skips trying to authenticate the user
and the request continues on like normal.</p>
<h3 id="getcredentials-build-the-form">getCredentials(): Build the Form <a class="headerlink" href="login-form-authenticator#getcredentials-build-the-form" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h3>
<p>If the user <em>is</em> trying to login, our <em>new</em> task is to fetch the username &amp; password
and return them.</p>
<p>Since we built a form, let's let the form do the work for us.</p>
<p>Normally in a controller, we call <code>$this-&gt;createForm()</code> to build the form:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="047e95cc70">
    <div class="meta">
